b'floating between stand up and acting... I decided to focus on both separately with the same depth of research and preparedness I bring to both separately. \nI am more patient these days and more present when hired for film or tv. Thankful that I\xe2\x80\x99ve been asked to'

b'vulnerability. I get such a kick out of volleying a scene with fellow actors. Stand up is juggling.. acting is dancing. Some of my earlier roles were standup related acting gigs. I stopped accepting those 7 or 8 years ago. It felt derivative. It also was weirdly'

b'Performance wise. For me one of the ultimate complements is when I get a call from the editor saying thank you for giving me so many nuanced options in terms of how we want to lay this out. I pride myself on telling the story with various degrees of intensity &'

b'A character you embody in a world choreographed by its director / writer (often times both at the helm) - quite simply you are a tool that needs to be well crafted in order for the visionary to call on you to bring their character to life and to offer up countless options....'
